-- Thailand Stocks: Airports of Thailand, Italian-Thai Development
-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 2012-01-12T09:52:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-12/charoen-pokphand-italian-thai-development-thai-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  Thailand   trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Bangkok.  The  SET Index (SET)  rose 0.1 percent to 1,052.23.  Airports of Thailand Pcl  (AOT TB), Thailand’s biggest
airfield operator, climbed 2.6 percent to 50 baht, halting a
two-day decline. Passenger traffic at its airports in December
jumped 25 percent from the previous month to 5.92 million,
according to the data on the company’s website.       Italian-Thai Development Pcl (ITD)  , the nation’s biggest
construction company, rose 1.7 percent to 3.66 baht, its biggest
gain since Dec. 2. The company may change the fuel supply for a
power plant in Myanmar after the government scrapped plans to
use coal, Somchet Thinaphong, managing director of Italian-
Thai’s Myanmar unit, said yesterday in an interview.  Kasikornbank Pcl (KBANK)  , the country’s third-largest
lender by assets, added 1.3 percent to 116.50 baht. Kasikorn
Asset Management Co., the bank’s mutual fund unit, plans to
boost assets under management by 22 percent to about 900 billion
baht in 2012, Ampol Polohakul, Kasikorn Asset’s executive
chairman, told reporters in Bangkok today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
